<subSubSection id="B2B665313163D90044E26AABFC441BC9" lastPageId="31" lastPageNumber="432" pageId="30" pageNumber="431" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="FA1336BA3163D90044E26AABFC441BC9" blockId="30.[151,1437,1809,2017]" lastBlockId="31.[151,1437,153,755]" lastPageId="31" lastPageNumber="432" pageId="30" pageNumber="431">
<emphasis id="C8D8EAA83163D90144E26AABFEDE1DDE" bold="true" box="[199,322,1989,2016]" pageId="30" pageNumber="431">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Pronotum with small, elongate, lateral black spots including posterolateral angles. Anterolateral margin of pronotum without solid black stripe and not punctured. Posterolateral angles developed, as long as interocular distance. Anterior margin of scutellum yellow (
<figureCitation id="62972A3F3162D900472B6DD3FCEF1AE9" box="[782,883,189,215]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="36.[151,250,1749,1774]" captionTargetBox="[181,1415,196,1699]" captionTargetId="figure@36.[151,1436,181,1723]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURE 20. Dorsal and ventral view. H. brachyacanthus A–B; H. infulatus C–D; H. leptacanthus E–F; H. tragelaphus G–H (Scale = 5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677909" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677909/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="432">Fig. 20E</figureCitation>
). Dorsal surface of abdomen brown. Connexivum green without spots, except distal margin of segment VII, dorsally urotergite 8 with inner black stripes continuing in free part of laterotergites 8 (
<figureCitation id="62972A3F3162D90045D36C6BFDC11B21" box="[502,605,261,287]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="36.[151,250,1749,1774]" captionTargetBox="[181,1415,196,1699]" captionTargetId="figure@36.[151,1436,181,1723]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURE 20. Dorsal and ventral view. H. brachyacanthus A–B; H. infulatus C–D; H. leptacanthus E–F; H. tragelaphus G–H (Scale = 5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677909" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677909/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="432">Fig. 20E</figureCitation>
). Ventrally apex of pseudosutures without rounded dark spots (
<figureCitation id="62972A3F3162D900410F6C6BFA0C1B21" box="[1322,1424,261,287]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="36.[151,250,1749,1774]" captionTargetBox="[181,1415,196,1699]" captionTargetId="figure@36.[151,1436,181,1723]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURE 20. Dorsal and ventral view. H. brachyacanthus A–B; H. infulatus C–D; H. leptacanthus E–F; H. tragelaphus G–H (Scale = 5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677909" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677909/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="432">Fig. 20F</figureCitation>
). Male (
<figureCitation id="62972A3F3162D90044C46C47FEB31B7D" box="[225,303,296,323]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1667,1692]" captionTargetBox="[171,1415,201,1606]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[151,1436,181,1641]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 15. H. leptacanthus. A–C Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—ventral view. D—Female, genital plates. E—metasternal process (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677899" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677899/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="432">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
A–C). Pygophore with dorsal rim barely excavated; lateral strongly projected posteriorly, surpassing posterolateral angles and expansions of ventral rim (
<figureCitation id="62972A3F3162D90046C36C23FCF51B59" box="[742,873,332,359]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1667,1692]" captionTargetBox="[171,1415,201,1606]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[151,1436,181,1641]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 15. H. leptacanthus. A–C Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—ventral view. D—Female, genital plates. E—metasternal process (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677899" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677899/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="432">Fig. 15A,B</figureCitation>
). Paramere with anterior lobe strongly developed, almost reaching base of proctiger; posterior lobe strongly developed and acuminated (
<figureCitation id="62972A3F3162D900406B6C1FFB281BB5" box="[1102,1204,368,395]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1667,1692]" captionTargetBox="[171,1415,201,1606]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[151,1436,181,1641]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 15. H. leptacanthus. A–C Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—ventral view. D—Female, genital plates. E—metasternal process (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677899" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677899/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="432">Fig. 15B</figureCitation>
). Proctiger with tufts of short setae widely separated, but not as much as in 
<taxonomicName id="3DAC4D393162D90046CE6CFBFC3C1B91" authorityName="Nunes &amp; Campos &amp; Mendonca &amp; Cunha &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Breddin" baseAuthorityYear="1904" box="[747,928,404,431]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oxyacanthus">
<emphasis id="C8D8EAA83162D90046CE6CFBFC3C1B91" bold="true" box="[747,928,404,431]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="432">H. oxyacanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Ventral rim with expansions well developed, barely tumid, and rounded (
<figureCitation id="62972A3F3162D90045EB6CD7FDA91BED" box="[462,565,440,467]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1667,1692]" captionTargetBox="[171,1415,201,1606]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[151,1436,181,1641]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 15. H. leptacanthus. A–C Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—ventral view. D—Female, genital plates. E—metasternal process (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677899" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677899/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="432">Fig. 15C</figureCitation>
). Female (
<figureCitation id="62972A3F3162D900468E6CD7FC8F1BED" box="[683,787,440,467]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1667,1692]" captionTargetBox="[171,1415,201,1606]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[151,1436,181,1641]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 15. H. leptacanthus. A–C Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—ventral view. D—Female, genital plates. E—metasternal process (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677899" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677899/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="432">Fig. 15D</figureCitation>
). Gonocoxites 8 inner angle covering base of gonocoxites 9. Laterotergites 9 wide, lightly surpassing sclerite uniting laterotergites 8.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B2B665313162D90044E26F6EFF4F18F1" pageId="31" pageNumber="432" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="FA1336BA3162D90044E26F6EFF4F18F1" blockId="31.[151,1437,153,755]" pageId="31" pageNumber="432">
<emphasis id="C8D8EAA83162D90044E26F6EFED31825" bold="true" box="[199,335,512,539]" pageId="31" pageNumber="432">Comments.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="9E3D4B4B3162D900457C6F6FFD881825" author="Breddin, G." box="[345,532,513,539]" pageId="31" pageNumber="432" pagination="135 - 153" refId="ref24439" refString="Breddin, G. (1904 a) Beitrage zur Systematik der Rhynchoten. Sitzungsberichte der Gesellschaft Naturforschender Freunde zu Berlin, 1904, 135 - 153." type="journal article" year="1904">Breddin (1904a)</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName id="3DAC4D393162D90046876F6FFCE31825" authorityName="Breddin" authorityYear="1904" box="[674,895,513,539]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Edessa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leptacantha">
<emphasis id="C8D8EAA83162D90046876F6FFCE31825" box="[674,895,513,539]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="432">Edessa leptacantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
related to 
<taxonomicName id="3DAC4D393162D90047DA6F6CFB221825" authorityName="Breddin" authorityYear="1904" box="[1023,1214,513,539]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Edessa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pachyacantha">
<emphasis id="C8D8EAA83162D90047DA6F6CFB8C1825" box="[1023,1040,514,539]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="432">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="C8D8EAA83162D90040046F6FFB221825" box="[1057,1214,513,539]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="432">pachyacantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName id="3DAC4D393162D90040C46F6CFA101825" authorityName="Nunes &amp; Campos &amp; Mendonca &amp; Cunha &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Breddin" baseAuthorityYear="1903" box="[1249,1420,513,539]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tragelaphus">
<emphasis id="C8D8EAA83162D90040C46F6CFA101825" box="[1249,1420,513,539]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="432">H. tragelaphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). These species can be differentiated by humeral angles globose in 
<taxonomicName id="3DAC4D393162D90047516F48FBAC1801" authorityName="Breddin" authorityYear="1904" box="[884,1072,549,575]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Edessa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pachyacantha">
<emphasis id="C8D8EAA83162D90047516F48FC191801" box="[884,901,550,575]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="432">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="C8D8EAA83162D90047B66F4BFBAC1801" box="[915,1072,549,575]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="432">pachyacantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="62972A3F3162D900401A6F4BFB341801" box="[1087,1192,549,575]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="36.[151,250,1749,1774]" captionTargetBox="[181,1415,196,1699]" captionTargetId="figure@36.[151,1436,181,1723]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURE 20. Dorsal and ventral view. H. brachyacanthus A–B; H. infulatus C–D; H. leptacanthus E–F; H. tragelaphus G–H (Scale = 5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677909" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677909/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="432">Fig. 20G</figureCitation>
). Other characters are subtle: expansions of ventral rim are more rounded, setae of lateral excavation of proctiger shorter, and paramere has anterior and posterior lobes more developed in 
<taxonomicName id="3DAC4D393162D90046F16F00FC1918B9" authorityName="Nunes &amp; Campos &amp; Mendonca &amp; Cunha &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Breddin" baseAuthorityYear="1904" box="[724,901,621,647]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leptacanthus">
<emphasis id="C8D8EAA83162D90046F16F00FC1918B9" box="[724,901,621,647]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="432">H. leptacanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
than in 
<taxonomicName id="3DAC4D393162D90047C56F00FB1418B9" authorityName="Nunes &amp; Campos &amp; Mendonca &amp; Cunha &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Breddin" baseAuthorityYear="1903" box="[992,1160,621,647]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tragelaphus">
<emphasis id="C8D8EAA83162D90047C56F00FB1418B9" box="[992,1160,621,647]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="432">H. tragelaphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The female of 
<taxonomicName id="3DAC4D393162D900411C6F00FF721895" authorityName="Nunes &amp; Campos &amp; Mendonca &amp; Cunha &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Breddin" baseAuthorityYear="1904" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leptacanthus">
<emphasis id="C8D8EAA83162D900411C6F00FF721895" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="432">H. leptacanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has four parallel narrow black stripes dorsally on seventh and eighth segments not found in 
<taxonomicName id="3DAC4D393162D90041386FFCFF5018F1" authorityName="Nunes &amp; Campos &amp; Mendonca &amp; Cunha &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Breddin" baseAuthorityYear="1903" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tragelaphus">
<emphasis id="C8D8EAA83162D90041386FFCFF5018F1" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="432">H. tragelaphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
